# Task Management Application  

## üìã Overview  
A full-stack task management application built with **Laravel (backend)** and **React (frontend)**. It features user authentication, CRUD operations for tasks, and a clean, responsive interface.  

---

## ‚ú® Features  

### ‚úÖ Backend (Laravel)  
- User registration & login with email/password  
- JWT-based authentication using Laravel Sanctum  
- CRUD operations for tasks  
- Task status management (pending, in_progress, done)  
- User-specific task access control  
- RESTful API design  
- Input validation & error handling  

### ‚úÖ Frontend (React + Vite + TypeScript)  
- Login & registration forms  
- Protected routes with authentication  
- Task list with pagination  
- Create, update, delete tasks  
- Status management with dropdown  
- Responsive design with Tailwind CSS  
- Loading & error states handling  
- Toast notifications  

### ‚úÖ Bonus Features  
- Docker setup for easy deployment  
- Pagination (10 tasks per page)  
- Protected frontend routes  
- Clean, professional UI  
- SQLite database for development  

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack  

### Backend  
- **Laravel 10.x** (PHP 8.1+)  
- **Laravel Sanctum** for authentication  
- **SQLite** (development) / **MySQL** (production)  
- RESTful API design  

### Frontend  
- **React 18** with TypeScript  
- **Vite** build tool  
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling  
- **React Router DOM** for routing  
- **Axios** for API calls  
- **React Hot Toast** for notifications  

---

## üöÄ Quick Start with Docker (Recommended)  

### 1. Clone and Setup  
```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd task-management-app

# Copy environment files
cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
cprontend/.env.example frontend/.env
---
2. Start with Docker Compose
# Start all services
docker-compose up -d

# Backend setup (in new terminal)
docker-compose exec backend composer install
docker-compose exec backend php artisan key:generate
docker-compose exec backend php artisan migrate
---
3. Access the Application

Frontend: http://localhost:5173
Backend API: http://localhost:8000
---
4. Stop the Application
docker-compose down
---
Manual Installation
Backend Setup
# Navigate to backend
cd backend

# Install dependencies
composer install

# Create environment file
cp .env.example .env

# Generate application key
php artisan key:generate

# Configure database in .env
DB_CONNECTION=sqlite
DB_DATABASE=/absolute/path/to/database/database.sqlite

# Create SQLite database
touch database/database.sqlite

# Run migrations
php artisan migrate

# Start development server
php artisan serve --port=8000
---
Frontend Setup
# Navigate to frontend
cd frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Configure environment
cp .env.example .env

# Start development server
npm run dev
---
üì° API Endpoints
Authentication

Method	Endpoint	Description
POST	/api/register	Register new user
POST	/api/login	Login user
POST	/api/logout	Logout user
GET	/api/user	Get authenticated user

Tasks (Protected)

Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/api/tasks	Get paginated tasks
POST	/api/tasks	Create new task
PUT	/api/tasks/{id}	Update task
DELETE	/api/tasks/{id}	Delete task
